issues.body:
Hi team,

It would be helpful to support annotating interface or controller methods as MCP (AI Tool) functions, for example:

`@RestController
public class TranslateController {

    @PostMapping("/translate")
    @McpTool(name = "Translate", description = "Translate Chinese to English", tags = {"translation"})
    public String translate(@RequestBody String text) {
        return translator.translate(text, "zh", "en");
    }
}
`
Annotating at the method level provides several advantages:

Better granularity: each method represents a distinct tool or capability.

Easier metadata extraction: parameters, return types, descriptions, etc.

Aligns with common patterns in tools like OpenAI Function Calling and LangChain.

This would allow agents or dispatchers to automatically discover and register available MCP tools
